abstract: President Donald Trump mocked the Democratic impeachment effort as he sought to rally supporters Tuesday in the key swing state of Pennsylvania, calling the process “impeachment lite” and promising it would lead to his reelection in 2020.
snippet: President Donald Trump mocked the Democratic impeachment effort as he sought to rally supporters Tuesday in the key swing state of Pennsylvania, calling the process “impeachment lite” and promising it would lead to his reelection in 2020.
lead_paragraph: HERSHEY, Pa. — President Donald Trump mocked the Democratic impeachment effort as he sought to rally supporters Tuesday in the key swing state of Pennsylvania, calling the process “impeachment lite” and promising it would lead to his reelection in 2020.
headline_main: Trump Mocks Impeachment Effort, Talks Up Trade Deal at Rally
headline_print_headline: Trump Mocks Impeachment Effort, Talks Up Trade Deal at Rally

abstract: The articles of impeachment offered up Tuesday against President Donald Trump are narrow, but consequential. They are also likely to be approved by Democrats alone.
snippet: The articles of impeachment offered up Tuesday against President Donald Trump are narrow, but consequential. They are also likely to be approved by Democrats alone.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The articles of impeachment offered up Tuesday against President Donald Trump are narrow, but consequential. They are also likely to be approved by Democrats alone.
headline_main: AP Analysis: Trump Faces Narrow but Consequential Charges
headline_print_headline: AP Analysis: Trump Faces Narrow but Consequential Charges

abstract: Democrats are planning to restrict their case to the Ukraine affair. Are they making a mistake?

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Democrats unveiled two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump on Tuesday, setting up a historic vote in the days before Christmas. abstract: It is the only thing to do if our country’s democracy is to survive.
snippet: It is the only thing to do if our country’s democracy is to survive.
lead_paragraph: Impeaching a president is the most consequential thing our Congress can do — other than declaring war. So, after great consideration, I say: President Trump not only should be impeached, he must be impeached if America’s democracy is to remain intact.
